Modules.Lord of the Grapes:
{{Main|Lord of the Grapes}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Daniel S. Donnelly]]
* '''Released:''' January 2000

Modules.No Place Like Home II:
{{Main|No Place Like Home II}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Daniel S. Donnelly]]
* '''Released:''' January 2000

Modules.Out for a Stroll:
{{Main|Out for a Stroll}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Daniel S. Donnelly]] and [[Tom Prusa]]
* '''Released:''' January 2000

Modules.The Scars that Never Heal:
{{Main|The Scars that Never Heal}}
{{Quote|One year ago, the devil princess Glasya battled an avatar of Sune Firehair on the streets of Ravens Bluff. Now, ''Glaysa's Poniard'', a dagger that marred a goddess of beauty, has returned to the city!}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Erik Mona]]
* '''Released:''' January 2000
''Sequel to ''[[Queen for a Day]]''.

Modules.Dreams of the Innocent:
{{Main|Dreams of the Innocent}}
{{Quote|Shalimarra Daradusk falls into an unnatural sleep, and you must come to her aid. But, there is another sleeper involved, and dreams mix with reality as you seek to free the young woman.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Todd Smart]]
* '''Released:''' January 2000
''Part 2 of "The New Darkness".''

Modules.No Time to Lose:
{{Main|No Time to Lose}}
{{Quote|Ravens Bluff must honor its treaty obligations, especially when the fate of the Prime Material plane may be at stake. Heroic deeds have become so routine that sometimes it seems that all the world is a stage and you are pawns in some grand cosmic game.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Paul Pederson]]
* '''Released:''' January 2000
''Adventure #5 in the "High-Level Planar Campaign".''

Modules.A Sunite Celebration:
{{Main|A Sunite Celebration}}
{{Quote|Many of the temple district's buildings were damaged last year at the Winter Festival as Sune and Glasya struggled in our fair streets. One of the most heavily damaged buildings was the Temple of Sune itself after the goddess sat upon it. Worshipers of the Lady of Love were worried that the temple would never be rebuilt. However news comes today of a titanic reopening gala to take place one year after the destruction of the temple. The spokeswoman for the temple of Sune had this to say: "We invite each and every citizen to experience the new Temple of Sune at the first anniversary of our lady's visit. We
promise song, romance, fun and games and delights to please all of the citizens of Ravens Bluff."}}
* '''Designer(s):''' 
* '''Released:''' January 2000

Modules.Stormbreaker:
{{Main|Stormbreaker}}
{{Quote|'''Low Level:''' Aleesia, High Moonmistress of the Full Moon, asks you if you would help finding and destroying a threat to her church (Selûne).<br />
'''High Level:''' Aleesia, High Moonmistress of the Full Moon, asks for your help in guarding the Stormbreaker, a war galley, on her maiden voyage.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Bill Reynolds]]
* '''Released:''' January 2000

Modules.When Ao Comes to Town:
{{Main|When Ao Comes to Town}}
{{Quote|A plague, their druid ran away, a minister of Ao, and now adventurers? Can this village's luck get any worse?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Matthew Capstraw]]
* '''Released:''' February 2000
''Part 1 of the "Ao" series.''

Modules.Crypt of the Unknown:
{{Main|Crypt of the Unknown}}
{{Quote|You are awoken from your nightmares and asked to find a young lady in mourning. However, the only answers seem to lie in a mysterious crypt. Can you survive the unknown chaos that lies within and return her home?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Christopher Reed]]
* '''Released:''' February 2000

Modules.Mist Opportunities:
{{Main|Mist Opportunities}}
{{Quote|Inclement weather in the Bluff leads to adventure, rewards, and a new enemy. Who knows where your choices will lead you? A crisis in the Underdark leads the Clerical Circle to make special demands of its members.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Clifford Caldwell]]
* '''Released:''' February 2000

Modules.To Hell in a Handbasket:
{{Main|To Hell in a Handbasket}}
{{Quote|It appears as if the Wizards Guild needs your help. Again. Looks like one of their agents has gone missing.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Stephen Wales]]
* '''Released:''' February 2000
''Part 3 of "The Saga of the Diabolical Grasp".''

Modules.Jerm Warfare:
{{Main|Jerm Warfare}}
{{Quote|Things have been disappearing all over Ravens Bluff and it's up to you to find them. In this adventure, you find that size does matter.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Kevin Blake]]
* '''Released:''' March 2000

Modules.An Average Day in Ravens Bluff:
{{Main|An Average Day in Ravens Bluff}}
{{Quote|Take a break from the hard life of adventuring and share a weekend with some friends. Relax, what could happen?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Laurie Fox]]
* '''Released:''' March 2000

Modules.The Dungeon of Sorrow:
{{Main|The Dungeon of Sorrow}}
{{Quote|Fate can sure be tricky sometimes. You would not have thought you would find yourself looking for the treasure of a dead dragon today, but here you are. Hopefully the rumors that the dragon is dead are true. Well, it's a break from saving the city, so in a sense it is an unexpected vacation. The question is whether you'll survive the "relaxation."}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Liz Black]]
* '''Released:''' March 2000

Modules.And the Deep Blue Sea:
{{Main|And the Deep Blue Sea}}
{{Quote|During the past couple of weeks, the number of sharks around Ravens Bluff has grown out of control. Shark attacks have occurred along the coast as far away as Procampur and Tantras and along the Fire River miles upstream from Ravens Bluff. Swimming has been banned, and the harbor has been closed to all ships smaller than 50 feet. Worst of all, Sharkie's has been closed [until] further notice.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Gary Labrecque]]
* '''Released:''' March 2000

Modules.Where Have All the Leaders Gone:
{{Main|Where Have All the Leaders Gone}}
{{Quote|In the wake of Carthoun's departure, Rendeth of the Royal Blood discovers that some important Procampan leaders are missing. He and Alissa turn to the adventuring community to solve the mystery, as the Diamond Legion is busy undoing the worst damage caused by the Star Guard.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Daniel Cooper]]
* '''Released:''' March 2000

Modules.A Piniago For Your Thoughts:
{{Main|A Piniago For Your Thoughts}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Daniel Cooper]]
* '''Released:''' March 2000

Modules.The Other Side of the Coin:
{{Main|The Other Side of the Coin}}
{{Quote|A competition between the Temples and Shrines of Procampur to earn funds for the local orphans is announced in the Shining Jewel. You all thought that perusing the various goods offered by the faithful would be interesting. But what does the Overgold of Waukeen want with you?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Matthew Domville]]
* '''Released:''' March 2000

Modules.Battlefield: Procampur:
{{Main|Battlefield: Procampur}}
{{Quote|The PCs are mysteriously transported to a Procampur that is completely unknown to them and are caught up in a plot not of their making. But the only way to figure out how to get home is to follow through with the task at hand: Save the city. Easy enough!}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Jay Fisher]]
* '''Released:''' March 2000
''Part 11 of the "Cracked Jewel Saga".''

Modules.Cenotaph:
{{Main|Cenotaph}}
{{Quote|A Griffon Knight has a personal request for adventurers to recover the remains of a lost comrade from a remote and possibly dangerous area. Are you game?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Peter Winz]]
* '''Released:''' March 2000

Modules.A Gruesome Faerie Tale:
{{Main|A Gruesome Faerie Tale}}
{{Quote|The Independent Individuals Association would like to send you on a quest for love into an enchanted forest. One of their members is in need of companionship, but is kind of shy. The forest holds the answer to his romantic dreams, but also a danger too gruesome to believe.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Brett King]]
* '''Released:''' March 2000

Modules.The Overlooked:
{{Main|The Overlooked}}
{{Quote|A request from a local innkeeper to help him discover what's going on in his Inn quickly turns into more than you expected. Much, much more. Suddenly Tantras seems to be turning into the city of undead, and you have to find a way to stop it. What sinister force could be behind all this?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Morrie Mullins]], [[Christy Nichols]], and [[Jae Walker]]
* '''Released:''' March 2000

Modules.Something in the Water:
{{Main|Something in the Water}}
{{Quote|The animals of Dark Hollow have started to undergo strange transformations. Can you discover the source of the problem before the citizens are affected too?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Rachael Casey]]
* '''Released:''' April 2000

Modules.The Eye of Horus:
{{Main|The Eye of Horus}}
{{Quote|Recently you have begun to settle into a fairly standard routine due an unusual lack of adventure in the area. However your routine is broken this morning as a pigeon lands upon your shoulder. The bird carries a note from the Mulhorandi embassy requesting assistance with a secret mission. Well it looks like it is time once again to don your adventuring gear!}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Larry Douglas]]
* '''Released:''' April 2000

Modules.First Link:
{{Main|First Link}}
{{Quote|Not everything that happens in the City of Ravens is plainly visible. Heinous crimes can always be found if one looks hard enough. But the motivations for these acts may be disturbing to some, and the solutions to the problems are never as easy as we would like.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Rick Brill]]
* '''Released:''' April 2000
''Part 1 of "Chain that Binds".''

Modules.Dragon's Spirit:
{{Main|Dragon's Spirit}}
{{Quote|A routine request to investigate a dragon battle to the north leads to the beginning of a quest that, if not completed, will cost far more than just a life.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Troy Daniels]] and [[Cindy Mullins]]
* '''Released:''' April 2000
''Part 1 of the "Cycle of Dragons" series.''

Modules.It's Your Lucky Day??:
{{Main|It's Your Lucky Day??}}
{{Quote|Something is happening at the gaming/adventurer's training club, The Stardust Inn. Is Lady Luck going to be with you when the Deputy Mayor personally asks you to get to the bottom of things. Players are encouraged to bring characters that have a history in Ravens Bluff, if they have one.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Gail L. Reese]]
* '''Released:''' April 2000
''Part 1 of "The Luck of Tyr".''

Modules.Close Quarters:
{{Main|Close Quarters}}
{{Quote|The city of Ravens Bluff has been nearly completely rebuilt following the war, and life is almost back to normal (whatever normal is). However, W.M. Ranke, one of the city merchants, has a bit of a problem with some lost workers. He's looking for a few heroes to help with his remodeling project. The task seems simple enough&mdash;but after all, this is Ravens Bluff&hellip;}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[J. Allan Fawcett]]
* '''Released:''' May 2000

Modules.If Only:
{{Main|If Only}}
{{Quote|As you return to Ravens Bluff, a chance encounter leads you to a ransacked village and lands you in the middle of a harrowing rescue attempt. Can you once again be the hero before it is too late?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Joseph Russell]]
* '''Released:''' May 2000

Modules.The Wizard's Game:
{{Main|The Wizard's Game}}
{{Quote|The population is abuzz with the news that a visiting wizard from another plane is challenging the citizens of Ravens Bluff to a game! Open tryouts will be held tomorrow morning, and anyone can participate. The proceeds from the spectators will benefit many of the city's charities. However, it looks like you won’t have a chance to participate, as the Wizards' Guild has summoned you for an important mission.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Gregory A. Dreher]]
* '''Released:''' May 2000

Modules.Cloud Nine:
{{Main|Cloud Nine}}
{{Quote|A retired adventurer is looking for adventurers to recover the body of a comrade lost in the cloud castle of an evil cloud giant.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Jim Roberts]]
* '''Released:''' July 2000

Modules.Dragon's Knowledge:
{{Main|Dragon's Knowledge}}
{{Quote|Draconic Lore speaks of a creature called the Dragon Sage. This creature holds the knowledge of all dragons and speaks in the riddles of the wyrm to give prophecy to all who would hear him. Information has been uncovered that leads you to far away lands to speak with him. But other forces are intent that you do not reach your destination so that an even darker prophecy may be fulfilled.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Troy Daniels]]
* '''Released:''' July 2000
''Part 2 of the "Cycle of Dragons" series.''

Modules.Dangerous Liaisons:
{{Main|Dangerous Liaisons}}
{{Quote|A wandering bard from a faraway land desperately needs your protection. It's too bad he won't accept your help!}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Brian Hancock]] and [[Sherry Hancock]]
* '''Released:''' July 2000

Modules.Everyone's Favorite Haunted House:
{{Main|Everyone's Favorite Haunted House}}
{{Quote|For one reason or another, you find yourself committed to spending a night in a haunted house.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Tracey Wilson]]
* '''Released:''' July 2000

Modules.Feat of Clay:
{{Main|Feat of Clay}}
{{Quote|You are in the area of Dragon Falls when word reaches you of an unstoppable death marching on the town, razing farms, slaying everything in sight. The local militia is demoralized and badly beaten. As heroes, naturally you step in to help. But what can stop this marching death, and can you find it in time?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Andrew Jaremkow]]
* '''Released:''' July 2000

Modules.Heart of Mohammed:
{{Main|Heart of Mohammed}}
{{Quote|Whispers abound in the gnomish community, and suddenly the name of the most infamous adventurer in Ravens Bluff's history is on everyone's lips again. But why, and what is behind this sudden resurgence of a dead adventurer? Can you lay Mohammed's reputation to rest once and for all?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Robert Wiese]]
* '''Released:''' July 2000
''Part 4 of the "Mohammed" series.''

Modules.Silk and Assassins:
{{Main|Silk and Assassins}}
{{Quote|The town of Hlintar is once again in need of your help. The thief gangs have squared off since your last visit, and now a gang war threatens to break out. The town will be devastated if you don't come and help.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Sean Duff]]
* '''Released:''' July 2000
''Part 2 of the "Corrupter" series.''

Modules.Approaching Doom:
{{Main|Approaching Doom}}
{{Quote|Dwarves&hellip;Cannibals&hellip;Human Sacrifice&hellip;An Ancient Evil&hellip;A New Evil?!? How could this be boring?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Frank Timar]] and [[Erika Timar]]
* '''Released:''' August 2000
''Part 1 of the "Destiny of the Dwarves" series.''

Modules.Eagle's Landing:
{{Main|Eagle's Landing}}
{{Quote|A golden eagle, oen of Procampur's most sacred symbols, falls from the sky into the city's Nobles District. But when the eagle turns up missing, will a sign that was once taken as a blessing be turned into a sign of ill-omen? It is up to Procampur's faithful to have the eagle restored before the city's own faith is irrevocably shattered.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Jay Fisher]] and the Universe Construction Company
* '''Released:''' August 2000

Modules.It Came From the Sea:
{{Main|It Came From the Sea}}
{{Quote|Storms ravage the Sea of Fallen Stars and cause terrible damage around Ravens Bluff. North in Mossbridges, it is hoped that the storms will drive out some smugglers which have been using the area as a base. You are asked to look for these smugglers and bring them to justice.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Daniel S. Donnelly]]
* '''Released:''' August 2000

Modules.Day of the Dwarf:
{{Main|Day of the Dwarf}}
{{Quote|The strange and bizarre are commonplace in the city of Ravens Bluff. Today though many of the city's inhabitants are in for a rude awakening. Who is behind it? Can we stop it? Is there a cure? These are just a few of the questions you need to answer! A role-playing intensive event.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Frank Timar]] and [[Erika Timar]]
* '''Released:''' September 2000
''Part 2 of the "Destiny of Dwarves" saga.''

Modules.Dragon's Deep:
{{Main|Dragon's Deep}}
{{Quote|Heading home from a mission in the Moonshae Isles you pass through the fabled City of Splendors, Waterdeep. Struggling to understand the dragon prophecy your party finds themselves caught into the intrigue, suspense and murder that has made this city famous. With the way that your luck has been recently, you might even see the Undermountain before this leg of your journey is over.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Troy Daniels]] and [[Jason Nichols]]
* '''Released:''' September 2000
''Part 3 of the "Cycle of Dragons" series.''

Modules.Revenge of the Cult:
{{Main|Revenge of the Cult}}
{{Quote|Strange events are afoot near the City of Ravens. You and your fellows are asked to investigate and seek out the source of the occurrences.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Michael White]]
* '''Released:''' September 2000
''Adventure #7 in the "High-Level Planar Campaign".''

Modules.The Stakeout:
{{Main|The Stakeout}}
{{Quote|A gang of thieves is terrorizing a local business. The watch cant seem to help. Can you get to the bottom of this crime?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Peter Parker]]
* '''Released:''' September 2000

Modules.Stanham Stone:
{{Main|Stanham Stone}}
{{Quote|A young farmhand has vanished abruptly in mysterious circumstances, and the alarmed landowner is hiring adventurers to find him and bring him back. Are you bold enough to step into the unknown to undertake the mission?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Andrew Jaremkow]]
* '''Released:''' September 2000

Modules.Back to the Hills:
{{Main|Back to the Hills}}
{{Quote|Misfortune has once again beset the village of Hill and Hallow, and monsters are ravaging the countryside. Can adventurers from Ravens Bluff protect them?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Matthew Capstraw]]
* '''Released:''' October 2000
''Part 2 of the "Ao" series.''

Modules.Built to Last:
{{Main|Built to Last}}
{{Quote|'''Low Tier:"''' You are asked to retrieve two halves of an ancient map from several long forgotten temples in hope that their recovery will lead to the answer for future events that as destined to go
bad for the citizens of Ravens Bluff.<br />
'''High Tier:''' Two pieces of an ancient map have been retrieved and you are called upon to take this now completed map and figure out where it leads and if its use can change events that may turn out disastrous.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Christopher Reed]]
* '''Released:''' October 2000

Modules.Cold Feat:
{{Main|Cold Feat}}
{{Quote|For the Redstone family to retain its lordly manor, there must be a legal heir&hellip; for there to be a legal heir, there must be a wedding&hellip; for there to be a wedding, there must be a groom&hellip; and that's proving to be a challenge.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Morrie Mullins]] and [[Cindy Mullins]]
* '''Released:''' October 2000

Modules.Mirror Maker:
{{Main|Mirror Maker}}
{{Quote|Heroes are needed to go giant hunting. Along the way there is a mystery to be solved, elves to visit, and devious traps to avoid.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Brian Wade]] and [[Kristofer Wade]]
* '''Released:''' October 2000

Modules.A Simple Pick Up:
{{Main|A Simple Pick Up}}
{{Quote|The wizard who hired you said that it would be a simple retrieval of an item for a local lord: a few days ride to Fallentree in the early fall just in time to see the foliage, and then back. But then again, who ever said anything was simple in Ravens Bluff?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Gary Labrecque]]
* '''Released:''' October 2000
''Part 2 of the "Torr" series.''

Modules.Wedding Day:
{{Main|Wedding Day}}
{{Quote|You received an invitation to a wedding this morning. It seems that the daughter adopted by the Murkos, Dawn of the Desert Moon, is getting married. Will this wedding go off without a hitch?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[David Samuels]]
* '''Released:''' October 2000

Modules.All Bad Things Must Come to an End:
{{Main|All Bad Things Must Come to an End}}
{{Quote|A band of noble adventurers is needed to remove a family curse, but can they do it in time to save the life of an innocent?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[John Bentas]]
* '''Released:''' November 2000

Modules.Dragon's Honor:
{{Main|Dragon's Honor}}
{{Quote|From Waterdeep the prophecy drives you to Westgate where the third key to the puzzle might be. Once there you find that that politics are not all they are cracked up to be. Especially when you find yourself caught in the middle of a conflict that you did not start. In order to succeed however, you and a new found friend must put a stop to it&hellip;}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Troy Daniels]] and [[Jason Nichols]]
* '''Released:''' November 2000
''Part 4 of the "Cycle of Dragons" series.''

Modules.Dwarf in the Fold:
{{Main|Dwarf in the Fold}}
{{Quote|The prophecies foretelling the return of the Dwarven Thane are being fulfilled, and now the dwarves take a hand in their own destiny. They seek to retrieve the lost Holy Symbol of Dugmarin Brightmantle, one of the artifacts needed to crown the thane. But there are those who oppose the emergence of the thane, and they will stop at nothing to keep you from success. Dwarven PCs recommended.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[David P. Santana]]
* '''Released:''' November 2000
''Part 3 of the "Destiny of the Dwarves" series.''

Modules.The Laws of Luck:
{{Main|The Laws of Luck}}
{{Quote|A very important amulet has been stolen from Lady Lauren DeVillars, the ''amulet of life protection'' that holds the soul of Sirrus Melandor. Can you find it and retrieve this important item?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Gail L. Reese]]
* '''Released:''' November 2000
''Part 2 of "The Luck of Tyr".''

Modules.The Stars Don't Lie:
{{Main|The Stars Don't Lie}}
{{Quote|"The death of many follow the fall of one." Is this vague message from the stars something worth worrying about or is it just someone's attempt to ruin our celebration? Let's find out&hellip;}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Lee Sharp]] and [[Michelle Sharp]]
* '''Released:''' December 2000
